text: Lee Ji-hye (born 21 October 1982) is a South Korean taekwondo practitioner. She won a gold medal in flyweight at the 2003 World Taekwondo Championships in Garmisch-Partenkirchen. She won a silver medal at the 2004 Asian Taekwondo Championships. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1982 births Category:Living people Category:South Korean female taekwondo practitioners Category:World Taekwondo Championships medalists Category:Asian Taekwondo Championships medalists
